data.value: 1. The setup file must be created if it has not been created once previously. 2. While setting up the courses, ensure that those are the maximum courses that are being taken by any student. For Example, if student A opts for 6 courses in a semester but student B opts for only 2 courses, then you should select 6 courses overall for the semester. You will later be able to skip unwanted courses. 3. Required information including Student Names / ID and Number of CLOs for each and every course must be entered. 4. PLO associated with each and every CLO must be entered. 5. The marks entered must be out of 100. 6. If a particular student is not taking any course then leave at least one dash on his marksheet of that specific course.
